    "title": "Front Office Manager - Radisson India Capital India - Top MNC",
    "description": "Join the Radisson India Capital India family as a Front Office Manager in Jabalpur. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Radisson India Capital India:\nRadisson India Capital India is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage front office operations including check-in/check-out\n• Plan and execute banquets, events, and MICE functions\n• Assist in menu planning, costing, and food festival coordination\n• Manage procurement of hotel supplies and control operating costs\n• Handle guest complaints and resolve issues promptly\n• Ensure compliance with FSSAI, health, and safety regulations\n• Coordinate with travel agents and OTAs for occupancy optimization\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Barista Skills\n• Proficiency in Tour Planning\n• Proficiency in Crisis Management\n• Proficiency in Revenue Management\n• Proficiency in PMS Systems\n• Proficiency in Housekeeping Standards\n• Proficiency in Opera PMS\n• Proficiency in Customer Relations\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Learning & development budget\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Radisson India Capital India!",
